rComments: Beth was the absolute BEST professor I ever had. Her class on Dante's Divine Comedy was incredible and I actually paid attention to her lectures because they were so interesting. She's so passionate about the subject that she makes you passionate about it as well. If she's teaching a class you owe it to yourself to take it because she's amazing.

I love Elisabeth Coggeshall. Before her class I not only knew nothing about Dante, I knew nothing about medieval Europe in general. Leaving Beths class I not only understood these subjects, but found a deep appreciation for Dante, Medieval Literature, and I found a greater understanding of Christianity as a whole. 10/10 Fantastic professor.

Beth's a really cool teacher, she's very passionate about Dante and all things literature. Her tests were tricky at first but she gave the class a way to get more points by writing an additional optional essay. I wasn't too excited about the material but she made class funny and entertaining. I'm very happy to have her as a teacher :)
